The paper discusses issues related to deep neural networks in natural-image spaces, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on dataset bias and perturbation, which are common concerns in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a new training method to improve the accuracy of a classifier, which falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the topological and geometric properties of natural-image spaces, which could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
